## 1. Purpose & Alignment
This ERS translates the Customer Requirements Specification (CRS v0.5) "Jane for Pool Maintenance Professionals" MVP (items 1–18) into testable, engineering-focused requirements. All SHALL statements in this document support one or more CRS MVP capabilities or foundational non-functional requirements.

### 1.1 Requirements Grammar
SHALL = mandatory. SHALL NOT = prohibition. SHOULD = strong preference (can be deferred with explicit justification). MAY = optional / stretch.

### 1.2 Traceability Overview
See Section 12 for full CRS→ERS traceability matrix. Every CRS MVP capability maps to at least one ENGINEERING requirement identifier (E-ID).
